# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Secrets — never commit real API keys
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# Editors / OS
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# Intentionally NOT ignored: data/ (downloaded PDFs) and chroma_db/ (the
# built vector index) — committing both means Streamlit Community Cloud can
# serve the app immediately with no separate build/ingestion step at deploy
# time. Fine at this project's small scale (a handful of PDFs); if the
# corpus grows much larger, revisit this and move ingestion into a build
# step instead of committing a large binary index.
